<task id="030" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add 4 tracking fields to sprk_analysisplaybook (lastindexedat, indexstatus, lastindexerror, indexhash)</title>
    <phase>2: WP1.5 Index Governance</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>027</dependencies>
    <blocks>031,034,035,036,037,039</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, solution, fields, schema</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Schema additions to production-bound entity; new files (publisher prefix) — STANDARD per task-execute Step 0.5 (no .cs/.tsx modification)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>2-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Same entity (`sprk_analysisplaybook`) as task 031; Dataverse PUBLISH ALL is global; serialize 030 → 031</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add 4 additive tracking fields to the `sprk_analysisplaybook` Dataverse entity per spec FR-08: `sprk_lastindexedat` (DateTime, nullable), `sprk_indexstatus` (OptionSet/Choice with values 'not-indexed' / 'pending' / 'indexed' / 'stale' / 'failed'), `sprk_lastindexerror` (Memo / Multiline Text up to 500 chars), `sprk_indexhash` (Text, 64 chars — sha256 hex). Use the `dataverse-create-schema` skill which covers what PAC CLI doesn't. Publish all customizations after addition.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE Dataverse schema engineer. Expert in `EntityDefinitions` Web API + the `dataverse-create-schema` skill pattern + Choice option-set lifecycle.</role>

  <goal>
    Four new fields live on `sprk_analysisplaybook`: `sprk_lastindexedat` (DateTime), `sprk_indexstatus` (Choice with 5 documented option values), `sprk_lastindexerror` (Memo, max 500 chars), `sprk_indexhash` (Text, max length 64). All four appear in Power Apps form designer. Solution export (CDS-Solution unmanaged zip) contains all four fields. No schema migration of existing rows required — fields are nullable / default to 'not-indexed'.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-08 + design §1.4 (WP1.5) + design.md "Tracking fields on `sprk_analysisplaybook` Dataverse row" section. These fields enable Send-to-Index UX (task 033), drift-detection job (task 034), admin view (task 035), and the validation gate (task 036). Adding 4 of the 5 planned fields here; `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata` is split out to task 031 because its JSON-schema documentation is a separate concern. Sequential within wave 2-A to avoid PUBLISH ALL race.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>docs/data-model/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-08 binding: 5 additive fields total on `sprk_analysisplaybook`; this task adds 4 (the 5th, `sprk_jpsmatchingmetadata`, is task 031).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">All fields additive — no breaking change; no migration of existing 6 production-bound playbooks required.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Reuse existing `sprk_playbookcode` (NVARCHAR(10)) — do NOT create new column; per CLAUDE.md Project-Specific MUSTs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT modify the 6 production-bound playbooks' output schemas / names / GUIDs (per spec §1.5).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-002">Schema additions go through solution; export resulting `sprk_AnalysisPlatform` solution unmanaged zip for downstream deploy task 039.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/design.md</file>
